<br>
France is still the #1 tourist destination for the US.  Point is, we like France, despite all the stereotypes.  Unfortunately, France appears to have an importance complex, and seem to be attempting to trying to prove themselves a key player.  I believe it backfired.  <br>
<br>
As much as we value our freedom of speech, I find it humorous when we turn visciously on those who express theirs.  But that is the way it works, I suppose.  <br>
<br>
Hearing on the radio that French's Mustard (British Company) was possibly facing boycott sent me straight for the aspirin.  I mean, come on, do your research before you start a boycott, please.  <br>
<br>
And don't believe everything you hear, no matter where it came from (remember, the news is typically left-wing and very biased).  You know the saying, &quot;the good guys always win&quot;?  Remember who writes the history books.  The losers, good or bad, aren't typically around to publish history.<br>
<br>
FYI, I believe we could have done much better foreign relations wise, but I think that had I been in charge, we would still be at war.  It seems to me a necessary evil.  I feel that we will only know the right decision in time.<br>
<br>
Bottles are good, miller-lite is bad.  <br>
